text: Wayne Harold Johnson (May 2, 1942 — October 16, 2020) was an American politician. He was a Republican member of the Wyoming Senate. He represented District 6 from 2005 until 2017. From 1993 to 2005, he was in the Wyoming House of Representatives. Johnson was born in El Paso, Texas. Johnson died on October 16, 2020 in Cheyenne, Wyoming at the age of 78.Wayne Johnson, “an example for others,” remembered for years of service to Cheyenne ==References== Category:1942 births Category:2020 deaths Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Politicians from Wyoming Category:Politicians from El Paso, Texas Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
